text: AEW Full Gear is a yearly professional wrestling pay-per-view (PPV) evenmade by All Elite Wrestling (AEW). The event started in 2019 and is held in the November time slot of AEW's pay-per-view calendar. It is one of AEW's big four pay-per-views. The name of the event is a reference to a segment from the YouTube series Being The Elite. ==Dates and venues== Event Date City Venue Main event Full Gear (2019) November 9, 2019 Baltimore, Maryland Royal Farms Arena Jon Moxley vs. Kenny Omega in an Unsanctioned Lights Out match. Full Gear (2020) November 7, 2020 Jacksonville, Florida Daily's Place Jon Moxley (c) vs. Eddie Kingston in an "I quit" match for the AEW World Championship. Full Gear (2021) November 13, 2021 Minneapolis, Minnesota Target Center Kenny Omega (c) vs. "Hangman" Adam Page for the AEW World Championship Full Gear (2022) November 19, 2022 Newark, New Jersey Prudential Center Jon Moxley (c) vs. MJF for the AEW World Championship Full Gear (2023) November 18, 2023 Inglewood, California Kia Forum MJF (c) vs. Jay White for the AEW World Championship. Full Gear (2024) November 23, 2024 Newark, New Jersey Prudential Center Jon Moxley (c) vs. Orange Cassidy for the AEW World Championship == References == Category:AEW Full Gear Category:2019 establishments in the United States
